  "executive_brief_md": "## ICOS \u2014 inducible T cell costimulator\n\n**White Space score 45.42/100 \u00b7 rank 3/13 \u00b7 MEDIUM confidence.** Top-tier white space \u2014 validated, tractable, and comparatively uncrowded within the IO cohort.\n\nICOS is a actin filaments target in the immuno-oncology cohort with no approved drug yet. Development level **Tchem**; mechanism: Inducible T-cell costimulator agonist; Inducible T-cell costimulator inhibitor. Competitive footprint: 4 industry sponsor(s) in trials. Leading disease associations: immunodeficiency, common variable, 1, common variable immunodeficiency, hypothyroidism, severe combined immunodeficiency.\n\n**Score decomposition** \u2014 Validation 0.7313, Tractability 0.9, Saturation 0.3099 (cohort-normalized). The score is multiplicative, so crowding drives it down even when biology is validated \u2014 which is why saturated checkpoints sit low and validated-but-uncrowded targets rise.\n\n*Every figure above resolves to a versioned source in the Provenance tab. This brief is model-written (claude-fable-5) over sourced facts only.*",
